// Edwin
@1 = ~I swear that Auril moves around the sun and not the opposite, Edwin.~
@2 = ~No! It's impossible!~
@3 = ~Even the wise Alaundo says in the third book of his "Mysteries Of the Sky" that...~
@4 = ~I remember the last mage that said something like that is now incapable of doing anything with a girl. But you probably use your tongue with women, so I should cut it off instead... Hehehe!~ [Female2a]
@5 = ~These simians! They always resort to the sword to settle an argument.~
@6 = ~Hehehe, but it seems a simple sword can get rid of a powerful mage.~ [Female2a]
@7 = ~Yes, but you, fool, have said nothing to explain to me why Auril Thorin goes around the sun. (Naturally, as it is a wrong, illogical and childish idea of your twisted mind)~
@8 = ~Don't think I've not heard you. I've seen in Irenicus's crystal orb that in the next two years an adept of Oghma will prove it. But if you pay me, mage, I will kill him before.~
// Viconia
@9 = ~Can I come with you too? I mean, I want to become a Drow. All that darkness, that bloodshed, that strife. I feel kinship to the Drow in my soul.~
@10 = ~You can color my skin and hair, so I will be perfect! Mary's drow-sheep, Beware! It's lamb chop time!~ [Innoc8]
// Edwin
@11 = ~Edwin, I think that we should consider the idea of having a relationship. You could be the brawn, while I would be the brain. It would be perfect!~
@12 = ~You should say that I am the brain and you the brawn. (These monkeys, they think they can rule only because they know how to eat bananas!)~
@13 = ~No, no, you cannot be the brain. You are too conceited, and remember, I have said I can hear your whispers.~
@14 = ~I think that stealing and blackmailing would pay well, and we could invest the profits in lamb farms.~
@15 = ~Even if I did stay with you, (and I don't want to), I would never waste my time and money on your damned Mommy's cows!~
@16 = ~They are Mary's lambs!~
@17 = ~Now that you are female you are even funnier, mage. I think we should become good friends.~
@18 = ~Haven't you any sympathy for my condition?~
@19 = ~Ed-win-a is falling down, falling down, falling down! Ed-win-a is falling down, oh my fair lady!~ [Female2a]
@20 = ~One of these days... One of these days... Ahh, why do I waste my time with you?~ [EDWINW21]
@21 = ~Because you like me!~
// Jaheira
@22 = ~Child, your actions are wild and dangerous to the group. Have you not found balance in your life?~
@23 = ~You may play the part of the innocent, but I fear you may have been tainted by your 'Master'.~
@24 = ~I'm tired of your balance-sickened speeches. I think the death of Khalid has made you bitter, like acid. Find a lover and don't bother me, darthiir elg'caress.~
@25 = ~Don't call me that, and never speak of Khalid again! You have not earned the right... You spread evil to everything you touch. You do this with pleasure and without thought. It is wrong. Don't you understand? Everytime you kill, you die a little bit yourself. Killing is not like eating sweets, you...~
@26 = ~This is my last word on the matter, bitch! Say anything else about thoughts or consequences and I will let you taste my poison.~
@27 = ~... or maybe I will ask the mage to polymorph you into a lamb.~
@28 = ~What? I want nothing to do with this! (She will be my damnation)~
@29 = ~<CHARNAME>! You heard what she said. Have you nothing to say to her?~
// Edwin & sex
@30 = ~So, mage, what is your attitude about ... ehm... love?~
@31 = ~Eh?~ [EDWINW22]
@32 = ~I mean, now that you are female, are you still attracted to women?~
@33 = ~That... is none of your business!~
@34 = ~Oh, maybe you have no time for women but like men better?~
@35 = ~Ah, and what do you know about that, fool?~
@36 = ~I know enough... I remember the time I was with the smugglers, there was a young woman named Black Rose. During the day she taught me how to cut throats, and during the night she had other businesses... I began to follow her every night to spy on her... Well, I think that I know more than a Drow priestess on sex.~
@37 = ~I don't think so. The Drow mastered the erotic arts eons ago.~ // viconia
@38 = ~Bah! Then you know nothing of love, at least of true love.~
@39 = ~This is what love is. It is deception. It is betrayal. It is worth nothing. I tracked her until she reached Baldur's Gate, but then I lost her. When I found her again she was dead. Someone else had killed her. Even vengeance was denied me!~
@40 = ~Now I have only my ambitions. I don't want love anymore. It is an illusion.~
@41 = ~Her name?~
@42 = ~I have cleared it from my mind.~
@43 = ~I think in the end you aren't so bad, mage. You have some good sides, only... you should love lambs more.~
// Viconia
@44 = ~Viconia, I want to learn something about your culture. Drows have fascinated me since my imprisonment.~
@45 = ~Keep your distance, surfacer, and learn to respect your elders.~
@46 = ~Please! And if I am a surfacer in the flesh, I am a Drow in my feelings! I like anything of the Drow. Drow clothing, Drow sun tan lotion and especially Drow coffee mugs.~
@47 = ~Very well. Then the first thing you should know is that in the Underdark, one with your tongue would die in less than one minute.~
@48 = ~Alright!~ [Female2a]
@49 = ~This is clearly the Master's work, but by the gods I have never seen anything so exquisite! Nobody does it better.~ [Female2a]
@50 = ~Alright, I will try another way. Viconia, please, can you teach me something about the Drow culture?~
@51 = ~Surfacer, what have I said about keeping your distance from me?~
@52 = ~Yes, I know, but I'm too interested.~
@53 = ~And why this morbid interest?~
@54 = ~Oh, let me think... What is most interesting to me is the Drow art of making poisons.~
@55 = ~Then you must ask a lowly Drow mage, not a noble priestess like me.~
@56 = ~Where can I find one of them?~
@57 = ~In an Underdark city, of course!~
@58 = ~That's a pity.~
// minsc-edwin added after 42
@59 = ~Dynaheir! You loved Dynaheir, and for revenge you tracked us to Baldur's Gate and tried to kill her! Boo thinks you should cover your eyes in shame.~ // Minsc if he is in party
@60 = ~(I don't know who is more intelligent, the man or the hamster)~
// jaheira
